      "content": "hey, so i've been re-reading some old classics lately like Moby Dick and i noticed something really weird. it's not even about the words themselves, but like... the actual spacing. the way certain gaps between sentences or paragraphs look different if you stare at them long enough. i feel like there's some kind of secondary layer of info hidden in the literal white space of the pages. like a hidden archive that isn't meant to be read with words. do you think that's actually possible from a structural standpoint?",
