      "content": "but that's just what the standard literary analysis tells us. if you look at how printing presses used to work back then, the physical ink-to-paper ratio wasn't always uniform. i'm not talking about \"visual ambiguity,\" i'm talking about actual patterns in the layout that seem almost mathematical. if someone wanted to hide a ledger or a history without being caught by censors, wouldn't using the negative space be the most genius way to do it? it's right there in plain sight because no one thinks to look at what ISN'T written.",
